.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-agent-setup - Create an agent profile interactively


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira agent setup  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Run an interactive wizard to create a new agent profile with:
  • Security tier (read-only, standard, admin)
  • Vault path glob restriction
  • Approval mode (prompt or deny)

.PP
The wizard creates a profile in config.yaml, a scoped token in the registry,
a token file, and outputs a ready-to-paste stdio MCP client configuration snippet.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for setup

.PP
\fB--write-config\fP[=false]
	write agent profile to config.yaml (always true in interactive mode)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-agent(1)\fP
